## 7. Service-to-Service Communication

### HttpClient Configuration

**Startup.cs**:

```csharp
services.AddHttpClient("user", client =>
{
    var userServiceUrl = Configuration.GetValue<string>("ServiceUrls:UserService");
    client.BaseAddress = new Uri(userServiceUrl);
    client.Timeout = TimeSpan.FromSeconds(30);
});
```

### Service Calls

#### To User Service

1. **Debit Wallet**:
   ```
   POST /api/users/{id}/wallet/debit
   Body: { amount: 4997 }
   Response: { id, balance }
   ```

2. **Credit Wallet**:
   ```
   POST /api/users/{id}/wallet/credit
   Body: { amount: 4997 }
   Response: { id, balance }
   ```

### Incoming Calls

#### From Order Service

1. **Process Payment**:
   ```
   POST /api/payments/process
   Body: { orderId, userId, userProfileId, amount }
   ```

2. **Refund Payment**:
   ```
   POST /api/payments/refund
   Body: { orderId, userId, userProfileId, amount }
   ```

